&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;United by Unique.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World Cancer Day 2026 is observed with the theme &amp;ldquo;United by Unique&amp;rdquo;, focusing on people-centred cancer care and individual experiences.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The theme &amp;ldquo;United by Unique&amp;rdquo; highlights that every cancer journey is different and deserves personalised care.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It emphasises placing people and their stories at the centre of cancer care systems.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The theme is part of a three-year campaign cycle run by the UICC.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It promotes equity, dignity and compassion in cancer prevention and treatment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;World Cancer Day&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Observed annually on 4 February.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Led by the Union for International Cancer Control.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aims to raise awareness, encourage prevention and improve access to cancer care.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Union for International Cancer Control&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Founded in 1933.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;A global organisation uniting cancer control organisations worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Runs World Cancer Day campaigns in three-year thematic cycles.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;Theme Cycle&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Allows deeper engagement with one core idea over multiple years.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Helps achieve sustained global impact in cancer awareness and advocacy.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Overcoming Disruption, Improving the AIDS Response.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World AIDS Day 2025 is observed with the theme &amp;quot;Overcoming Disruption, Improving the AIDS Response&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The theme highlights the importance of transforming HIV services to be more equitable and community-led.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It focuses on overcoming disruptions caused by conflicts, epidemics, and inequalities affecting access to care.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It emphasizes preserving past progress while accelerating improvements in HIV/AIDS response systems.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The theme aligns with India&amp;#39;s ongoing efforts through NACO and NACP to strengthen prevention, testing, and treatment services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex; gap: 6px; align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle; font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World AIDS Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Observed every year on&lt;strong&gt; 1 December.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;First established by the World Health Organization in 1988.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Aims to raise awareness and support people living with HIV/AIDS.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;NACO (National AIDS Control Organization)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Nodal body for implementing HIV/AIDS prevention and treatment programmes in India.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Operates under the Ministry of Health and Family Welfare.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UNAIDS 95-95-95 Target&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;95% of people living with HIV know their status.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;95% of diagnosed individuals receive sustained ART.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;95% of people on ART achieve viral suppression.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Uniting with Youth Against Corruption: Shaping Tomorrow&amp;#39;s Integrity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International Anti-Corruption Day is observed annually on 9th December.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The 2025 celebration focuses on youth participation in anti-corruption initiatives.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The official theme for 2025 is &amp;quot;Uniting with Youth Against Corruption: Shaping Tomorrow&amp;#39;s Integrity&amp;quot;.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The campaign emphasizes empowering youth to fight corruption.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Focuses on using technology, education, and social media as tools.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Aims to build ethical governance with active youth involvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display:flex;gap:6px;align-items:center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-size:21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UNODC&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &amp;ndash; United Nations Office on Drugs and Crime, responsible for coordinating global anti-corruption efforts.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;UNDP&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &amp;ndash; United Nations Development Programme, supports governance reforms worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Awareness events include webinars, workshops, and campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The day aims to promote transparency and accountability globally.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Local Youth Actions for the SDGs and Beyond&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;International Youth Day: 12 August.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;292&quot; data-start=&quot;218&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;292&quot; data-start=&quot;220&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;247&quot; data-start=&quot;220&quot;&gt;International Youth Day&lt;/strong&gt; is celebrated on &lt;strong data-end=&quot;278&quot; data-start=&quot;265&quot;&gt;August 12&lt;/strong&gt; every year.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;347&quot; data-start=&quot;293&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;347&quot; data-start=&quot;295&quot;&gt;Established by the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;332&quot; data-start=&quot;314&quot;&gt;United Nations&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong data-end=&quot;344&quot; data-start=&quot;336&quot;&gt;1999&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;388&quot; data-start=&quot;348&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;388&quot; data-start=&quot;350&quot;&gt;First observed in the year &lt;strong data-end=&quot;385&quot; data-start=&quot;377&quot;&gt;2000&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;461&quot; data-start=&quot;389&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;461&quot; data-start=&quot;391&quot;&gt;Aims to &lt;strong data-end=&quot;412&quot; data-start=&quot;399&quot;&gt;recognise&lt;/strong&gt; and &lt;strong data-end=&quot;428&quot; data-start=&quot;417&quot;&gt;empower&lt;/strong&gt; young voices on global issues.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;526&quot; data-start=&quot;462&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;526&quot; data-start=&quot;464&quot;&gt;2025 theme: &lt;strong data-end=&quot;523&quot; data-start=&quot;476&quot;&gt;Local Youth Actions for the SDGs and Beyond&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The Correct Answer is&amp;nbsp;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Answering the Call&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&amp;nbsp;World Organ Donation Day: 13 August.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;246&quot; data-start=&quot;105&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;246&quot; data-start=&quot;107&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;135&quot; data-start=&quot;107&quot;&gt;World Organ Donation Day&lt;/strong&gt; is observed on &lt;strong data-end=&quot;164&quot; data-start=&quot;151&quot;&gt;August 13&lt;/strong&gt; every year to raise awareness about &lt;strong data-end=&quot;219&quot; data-start=&quot;201&quot;&gt;organ donation&lt;/strong&gt; and dispel misconceptions.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;300&quot; data-start=&quot;247&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;300&quot; data-start=&quot;249&quot;&gt;The theme for &lt;strong data-end=&quot;271&quot; data-start=&quot;263&quot;&gt;2025&lt;/strong&gt; is &lt;strong data-end=&quot;299&quot; data-start=&quot;275&quot;&gt;&amp;ldquo;Answering the Call&amp;rdquo;&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;449&quot; data-start=&quot;301&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;449&quot; data-start=&quot;303&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;325&quot; data-start=&quot;303&quot;&gt;Ronald Lee Herrick&lt;/strong&gt; was the first person to donate his kidney to his twin brother in &lt;strong data-end=&quot;399&quot; data-start=&quot;391&quot;&gt;1954&lt;/strong&gt;, making it the first successful organ transplant.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;642&quot; data-start=&quot;450&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;642&quot; data-start=&quot;452&quot;&gt;&lt;strong data-end=&quot;473&quot; data-start=&quot;452&quot;&gt;Dr. Joseph Murray&lt;/strong&gt; performed this groundbreaking kidney transplant and later received the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;587&quot; data-start=&quot;545&quot;&gt;Nobel Prize in Physiology and Medicine&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong data-end=&quot;599&quot; data-start=&quot;591&quot;&gt;1990&lt;/strong&gt; for advancements in organ transplantation.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;812&quot; data-start=&quot;643&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;812&quot; data-start=&quot;645&quot;&gt;In &lt;strong data-end=&quot;657&quot; data-start=&quot;648&quot;&gt;India&lt;/strong&gt;, &lt;strong data-end=&quot;681&quot; data-start=&quot;659&quot;&gt;National Organ Day&lt;/strong&gt; was observed on &lt;strong data-end=&quot;713&quot; data-start=&quot;698&quot;&gt;November 27&lt;/strong&gt; from 2010 to 2022, initiated by the &lt;strong data-end=&quot;811&quot; data-start=&quot;750&quot;&gt;National Organ and Tissue Transplant Organization (NOTTO)&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li data-end=&quot;973&quot; data-start=&quot;813&quot;&gt;
	&lt;p data-end=&quot;973&quot; data-start=&quot;815&quot;&gt;In &lt;strong data-end=&quot;826&quot; data-start=&quot;818&quot;&gt;2023&lt;/strong&gt;, India shifted its &lt;strong data-end=&quot;868&quot; data-start=&quot;846&quot;&gt;Organ Donation Day&lt;/strong&gt; to &lt;strong data-end=&quot;884&quot; data-start=&quot;872&quot;&gt;August 3&lt;/strong&gt; to commemorate India&amp;rsquo;s first &lt;strong data-end=&quot;960&quot; data-start=&quot;914&quot;&gt;successful deceased-donor heart transplant&lt;/strong&gt; in &lt;strong data-end=&quot;972&quot; data-start=&quot;964&quot;&gt;1994&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Translation, shaping a future you can trust.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The theme for International Translation Day 2025 is &amp;quot;Translation, shaping a future you can trust.&amp;quot;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International Translation Day is celebrated on 30 September, the feast day of St. Jerome, the patron saint of translators.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The day was declared by the United Nations General Assembly in 2017, recognizing the role of language professionals in connecting nations.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The theme emphasizes the vital role of translation in shaping a trustworthy and interconnected future.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Translation plays a key role in fostering peace, understanding, and development across global communities.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;color: rgb(0, 0, 0);&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;International Translation Day&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Declared by the UN General Assembly on 24 May 2017 to highlight the importance of translators and language professionals.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;font-weight: bolder;&quot;&gt;St. Jerome&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/u&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;St. Jerome, the patron saint of translators, is celebrated on 30 September for his work in translating the Bible.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;strong&gt; &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;21 September&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The International Day of Peace 2025, also known as World Peace Day, is observed globally on 21 September each year.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;World Peace Day was established by the United Nations General Assembly in 1981, with 21 September designated as the permanent date in 2011.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The theme for 2025 is &amp;ldquo;Act Now for a Peaceful World,&amp;rdquo; emphasizing proactive steps to promote peace, empathy, cooperation, and diversity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Annual events include peace marches, educational workshops, cultural programs, and sports events aimed at promoting peace and resolving conflicts.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The UN Peace Bell, a gift from Japan, is rung each year at the UN Headquarters in New York as a symbolic gesture of global solidarity.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance of the Day&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;World Peace Day encourages resolving disputes through dialogue, supports non-violence, and promotes global unity and understanding.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Educational Programs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Schools and universities across the world organize programs to instill empathy, tolerance, and respect for others.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Supporting the SDGs&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;World Peace Day aligns with the United Nations Sustainable Development Goals (SDGs), particularly those focusing on peace, justice, and equality.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;International Events&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Peace marches, cultural programs, community dialogues, and symbolic acts like candlelight vigils are organized worldwide.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The correct answer is &lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Eat Right for a Better Life.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/in_news.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;In News&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Nutrition Week 2025 in India will focus on the theme &lt;u&gt;&amp;ldquo;Eat Right for a Better Life&amp;rdquo;&lt;/u&gt;, highlighting the importance of balanced diets, mindful eating, and preventing malnutrition and lifestyle-related diseases.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The &lt;u&gt;theme&lt;/u&gt; emphasizes adopting &lt;u&gt;balanced diets&lt;/u&gt; with fresh, seasonal foods and reducing consumption of junk food and processed items.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Encourages &lt;u&gt;mindful eating&lt;/u&gt;, portion control, and cooking nutritious meals for long-term health.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This theme complements India&amp;rsquo;s &lt;u&gt;POSHAN Abhiyaan&lt;/u&gt; and Mid-Day Meal Scheme, which aim to tackle malnutrition and diet-related diseases.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Nutrition Week aims to reach communities, schools, and households, fostering nutrition education at every level.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/additional-information-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt; &lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Additional Information&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;National Nutrition Week History&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;

	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Introduced in &lt;u&gt;1982&lt;/u&gt; by the Food and Nutrition Board under the Ministry of Women &amp;amp; Child Development to raise awareness about balanced diets.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;India&amp;rsquo;s Nutrition Challenges&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;India faces a &lt;u&gt;triple burden of malnutrition&lt;/u&gt;: undernutrition, micronutrient deficiencies, and diet-related chronic diseases.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Activities During NNW 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Activities like Healthy Tiffin Days, workshops on balanced diets, nutrition screening, and cooking demonstrations will be organized.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Government Initiatives&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;POSHAN Abhiyaan&lt;/u&gt; focuses on reducing &lt;u&gt;undernutrition&lt;/u&gt;, &lt;u&gt;anemia&lt;/u&gt;, and &lt;u&gt;stunting&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Mid-Day Meal Scheme&lt;/u&gt; ensures nutritious meals for schoolchildren, contributing to better health outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;Anganwadi Centres&lt;/u&gt; provide nutrition counselling and distribute fortified foods to children and pregnant women.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;u&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Significance of NNW 2025&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/u&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Reinforces India&amp;rsquo;s commitment to achieving the UN Sustainable Development Goal of &lt;u&gt;Zero Hunger&lt;/u&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Promotes healthy lifestyle choices to combat &lt;u&gt;non-communicable diseases&lt;/u&gt; and encourages inclusive awareness across all demographics.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

